<%- include("templates/header")%>
<div class="">
    <h1 class="fw-bold text-center my-3">Thanks for choosing mytrAIner</h1>
    <h4 class="fw-bold text-center my-3">To get started simply fill out the form below with your information!</h4>
    <form class="setup-form" >
    <div class="card-body" style="width:60vw; margin:0 auto;">
        <div class="row grid">
            <div class="col-2 g-start-8" style="margin: 0 auto">
              <input type="number" name="age" id="age" class="form-control" placeholder="Age" aria-label="Age">
            </div>
            
                <select id="gender" class="form-select col-3" style="margin: 0 auto" aria-label="Defa3lt select example">
                    <option selected>Gender</option>
                    <option value="Male">Male</option>
                    <option value="Female">Female</option>
                    <option value="undisclosed">Rather not say</option>
                  </select>
            
          </div>
          <div class="row grid my-3">
            <div class="col-3" style="margin: 0 auto">
              <label class="form-label">Weight in lb</label>
            <input id="weight" type="number" class="form-control">
            </div>
            <div class="col-3" style="margin: 0 auto">
              <label class="form-label">Height</label>
              <input id="feet" type="number" class="form-control" placeholder="feet">
              <input id="inches" type="number" class="form-control" placeholder="inches">
            </div>

          </div>
          
            <div class="my-3">
                <label for="exampleFormControlTextarea1" class="form-label">Please state your goals for using this app</label>
                <textarea id="goals" class="form-control" id="exampleFormControlTextarea1" rows="3"></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="py-3">
                <p class="fw-bold">on a scale of 1 through 10 with 10 being very experience and 1 being no experienced, how experienced are you in exercise?</p>

                <input type="range" value="5" min="1" max="10" oninput="this.nextElementSibling.value = this.value">
                <output id="experience">5</output>
            </div>

            <div>
                <h4 class="fw-bold text-center mt-3"></h4>
                
                  <p class="fw-bold">Choose one or more Exercise types that you enjoy</p>
                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="cardio" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="cardio">
                        Cardiovascular exercises: These are exercises that increase your heart rate and breathing rate, such as running, cycling, swimming, and jumping jacks.
                    </label>
                  </div>
              
                  <!-- Checked checkbox -->
                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="strength" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="strength">
                        Strength training exercises: These are exercises that involve resistance to build and strengthen muscles, such as weightlifting, push-ups, pull-ups, and squats.
                    </label>
                  </div>
              
                  <!-- Checked checkbox -->
                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="flexibility" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="flexibility">
                        Flexibility exercises: These are exercises that improve your range of motion and flexibility, such as yoga, Pilates, and stretching.
                    </label>
                  </div>
                
                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="balance" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="balance">
                        Balance exercises: These are exercises that improve your stability and balance, such as standing on one leg, yoga poses, and balancing on a stability ball.
                    </label>
                  </div>

                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="high-intensity" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="high-intensity">
                        High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT): These are exercises that alternate periods of high-intensity exercise with periods of rest or low-intensity exercise, such as sprinting, burpees, and jumping jacks.
                    </label>
                  </div>

                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="low-impact" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="low-impact">
                        Low-impact exercises: These are exercises that are easy on your joints, such as walking, cycling, and swimming.
                    </label>
                  </div>

                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="sport" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="sport">
                        Sports-specific exercises: These are exercises that are designed to improve your performance in a specific sport, such as basketball, football, or tennis.
                    </label>
                  </div>

                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="functional" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="functional">
                        Functional training exercises: These are exercises that simulate movements you use in everyday life, such as lifting groceries or bending down to pick up a child, and can improve your overall strength and flexibility.
                    </label>
                  </div>

                  <div class="form-check py-3">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="bodyweight" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="bodyweight">
                        Bodyweight exercises: These are exercises that use your own body weight as resistance, such as push-ups, pull-ups, squats, and lunges.
                    </label>
                  </div>

                  <div class="form-check">
                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="endurance" />
                    <label class="form-check-label" for="endurance">
                        Endurance exercises: These are exercises that improve your ability to sustain physical activity over a long period of time, such as long-distance running, cycling, or swimming.
                    </label>
                  </div>
                
              </div>
         
        <div class="card-footer text-end">
          <button type="button" onclick="generatePrompt()"></button>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
  <script src="js/generatePrompt.js"></script>
<%- include("templates/footer")%>